# Database Rules

## Source of Truth

`data/sovereign.db` is the single source of truth for all transactions.
The CSV (`data/transactions_sample.csv`) is a **seed file only** — it is imported
once on first run via `seed_from_csv()` and never read again after that.

Do not reintroduce `pd.read_csv()` calls in `PortfolioManager.load_transactions()`.

## Adding Transactions

All new trades must go through `TransactionStore.add_transaction()` or
`PortfolioManager.add_transaction()`. Never INSERT directly with raw SQL
outside of `TransactionStore`.

```python
# ✅ CORRECT
pm.add_transaction("2026-04-01", "buy", "Apple Inc", "AAPL",
                   price=172.50, quantity=5, amount=-862.50)

# ❌ WRONG — bypasses null handling and type normalisation
conn.execute("INSERT INTO transactions VALUES (...)")
```

## Schema Contract

| column     | type    | notes |
|------------|---------|-------|
| date       | TEXT    | ISO-8601 e.g. "2025-08-05" |
| type       | TEXT    | always lowercase: buy/sell/dividend/income/expense |
| quantity   | REAL    | always positive — direction implied by type |
| amount     | REAL    | signed cash impact (negative = outflow) |

Never rename these columns — `load_transactions()` maps them directly to
the pandas DataFrame schema expected by `PortfolioManager`.

## NULL Handling

Use `TransactionStore._null()` to convert NaN, empty strings, and "nan"
strings to Python `None` before any INSERT. SQLite stores `None` as NULL.

## WAL Mode

The database always opens with `PRAGMA journal_mode = WAL`.
Do not change this — it allows safe concurrent reads during pipeline runs.
